nodes.directive:
Create workspace for task execution {{task_name}}.

Path format: ./moira-ws/{task-name}-{YYYYMMDD}-{HHMM}/  (must end with a trailing slash)
Example: ./moira-ws/auth-fix-20251212-1030/

1) Create the workspace folder with the current date and time
2) Save the current workflow process ID to {workspace}process-id.txt for recovery after archival
3) Create {workspace}task-requirements.md with:
   - Task description: {{understand-task.task_description}}
   - Expected result: {{understand-task.expected_deliverable}}
   - Success criteria: {{understand-task.success_criteria}}
   - Constraints: {{understand-task.constraints}}
4) Create {workspace}planning-standards.md with:
   {{planning_standards}}

Return workspace_path ending with a trailing slash. Confirm workspace creation.

Break down task '{{understand-task.task_description}}' into specific executable steps.

Requirements:
- As many steps as the task genuinely needs — small tasks may have a few, large tasks may have 20-40. Do NOT pad or truncate the plan to hit a target number; let the task's real scope decide.
- Each step = one specific action
- For each step specify expected_output (how to verify step is complete)
- Steps should lead to deliverable: {{understand-task.expected_deliverable}}

Planning standards:
{{planning_standards}}

{{#if has_file_access}}Save the plan to {{workspace_path}}/plan.md in readable markdown (one numbered item per step). Return only total_steps and plan_saved_to_file — do NOT echo the plan back.{{else}}NO file access: you MUST return the full steps[] array AND current_step_action + current_step_expected_output of step 1 — the plan lives only in context (there is no plan.md).{{/if}}

CRITICAL: FIX THE ISSUES — NO REPORTS!

Fix all plan validation issues completely.

{{#if has_file_access}}READ {{workspace_path}}/plan-validation-issues.md{{else}}Issues from context: {{validate-plan.validation_issues}}{{/if}}

For EACH issue: understand it, apply the fix completely (no partial fixes), verify it is resolved.
Reviewer findings are authoritative — do not skip any, even minor ones.

Planning standards:
{{planning_standards}}

{{#if has_file_access}}After fixing, update {{workspace_path}}/plan.md. Return only fixes_applied — do NOT echo the plan.{{/if}}

